<p>This paper describes the Army's long range precision fires (LRPF) capabilities, their demonstrated value in joint operations, potential LRPF roles in the evolving joint operating environment, and Army modernization initiatives to adapt them to joint commanders' future needs</p>
<p>The Army's LRPF capabilities are the longer range (270+ km) Army Tactical Missile System (ATACMS) and the shorter range (70+ Km) Guided Multiple Launch Rocket System (GMLRS) - both launched from the same two air-transportable, ground mobile systems.  They are uniquely versatile complements to the mix of joint munitions available to division, corps and joint units - enabling them to immediately employ significant quantities of highly responsive, all-weather, long range precision fires across the range of military operations.  GMLRS and ATACMS variants deliver either a single high explosive "unitary" or cluster munition warhead against point and area targets.</p>
<div class="blockCallout" id="alignRt">
			<div class="blockimage"><asp:HyperLink runat="server"
