			</div>
<p>In Korea, these systems have represented the greatest quantity of forward positioned, immediately available joint long range munitions available to deter and respond to North Korean aggression.  In OIF ATACMS effectively neutralized enemy IADS, enabling achievement of initial air superiority; ATACMS and GMLRS played key roles supporting rapid land forces maneuver. In Iraq and Afghanistan over 3000 GMLRS and 85 ATACMS have been fired in support of joint combat operations. Their demonstrated precision has made them invaluable in urban terrain, where collateral damage is sometimes a concern.  Special operations forces, in particular, have relied upon them as unique, air-transportable, highly responsive means to conduct raids - delivering out-of-nowhere devastating effects against both area and point time-sensitive targets at long range – whenever and wherever needed.</p>
